## Important Patterns

- **Svelte 5 runes**: All state uses `$state()`, `$effect()`, `$props()` ŌĆö no legacy `$:` or stores
- **Unified agent loop**: Server runs one `pydantic-ai` agent with 4 tools. Code editing is a tool (`edit_diagram`) not a default output ŌĆö the agent chooses whether to edit code, enhance visually, or just respond with text. Client-side tools (`render_and_capture`, `capture_screenshot`) execute via WS tool_request/tool_result protocol. Auto-fix is handled by the agent (it sees render errors and retries).
- **AgentDeps**: Dataclass injected via `RunContext[AgentDeps]`. Contains the WebSocket + pending tool futures. `request_client_tool()` sends a WS message and awaits the response via `asyncio.Future`.
- **Tab content persistence**: Preview uses `style:display` (not `{#if}`) so both Mermaid SVG and Enhanced panels stay in DOM
- **Editor focus ŌåÆ Mermaid tab**: Clicking/focusing the code editor automatically switches the preview to the Mermaid tab
- **Agent tools**: `read_mermaid_syntax`, `read_mermaid_config` (server-side docs), `edit_diagram` (renders code via client-side `render_and_capture`), `enhance_diagram` (server-side image gen)
- **No Enhance button**: Enhancement is triggered by the agent when appropriate (user asks via chat). No manual Enhance button in the UI.

## Tests

- **Backend**: `pytest` ŌĆö `backend/tests/test_api.py` (REST + WebSocket endpoints), `test_agent.py` (tool functions). Run: `cd backend && uv run pytest`
- **Frontend**: Playwright e2e ŌĆö `frontend/test/e2e.spec.ts`. Run: `cd frontend && npx playwright test`
- **WSL2 note**: E2E tests block Google Fonts (`blockExternalRequests`) and wait for `[data-hydrated]` to handle SSR hydration timing.

## Environment

- `backend/.env`: `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_MODEL` (default gemini-2.5-flash), `ENHANCE_MODEL` (default gemini-2.5-flash-preview-04-17)
- No `python` binary in WSL2 ŌĆö use `uv run python` or `python3`
